rComments: Very bad professor, not comprehensive at all, very bad explainer.
he is not helpful at all, his classes sometimes are not boring :)

WORST PROF EVER!!! Worst part is he is the only one who teachs this course, I swear if you could take it at another university I would do that.  Made my life hell, has no appreciation for students who put an effort in his class, hardest marker, does not care about students.  I hate him :)

Hardest Prof ever. Does not make his own assignments nor quizes. This means that they were not covered in class so in order to solve them, you would need to look beyond what u were tought. RIDICULOUS!!! Also very boring and goes through material very fast so you don't understand anything! AVOID this dude, believe me!

He started out with a decent teaching style, reviewing each chapter as he finished it, and making a set of notes for each. But after chapter 3, he completely lost all organization and ability to stimulate any interest in the class. The labs were a pain in the ass, but the final wasn't too bad. Complete hardass about attendance during presentations.

He spends the entire lecture copying what is in his notes onto the board. The entire class then copies these unreadable notes off of the board. That is the class. That is all the goes on. He spends no time explaining what he's written down. It reminds me of elementary school all over again. That's where he should be teaching.

He is the worst professor I have ever had!! Doesn't know much, does not even try to explain properly.. All he does is staring at his notes and mumble. Never prepares his own class notes, labs or assignments. Always gets them from other profs or steals them from the web. On top of all these things, he is very cocky and unfair.
Avoid him as much as you can. He knows nothing and the funny thing that he steals exam questions that he even can't solve.

Can't teach at all in English? just reading? what's the purpose of asking people to do presentations if they don't have the proper knowledge? it's a 3rd engineering class not ESL class? I hope that he will improve and be more easy in the future.
Distributed Systems is an interesting topic, yet he managed to put me to sleep every single class.  Also the type of testing is pure definitions, which I don't think is appropriate for this course.

Poor prof. If you hate going to a class where the professor reads things out to you, avoid his courses. If you're resourceful, you'll do fine in his course. Everything he asks is available on the internet -- the catch? You won't learn anything. I'm 24+ years old, and pay a fortune for tuition. I don't need you taking attendance. It's not Gr. 4.

Cannot teach at all. Just reads the book and uses someone elses examples (even ones that have mistakes and we then have to correct him) terrible. a lot of the final was really different from the stuff he tought, I highly doubt he would be able to solve it if he didn't steal the questions and solutions from someone else. avoid if you can
crappy.  Makes quizes and tests stupidly long and can't teach.  takes attendance for presentations he makes the students do so he has less work.
I don't know what to say, but learn on your own. Its a lot better. Don't come to class expecting to learn anything. Don't expect an easy class at all.

The worst human been ever. The material is easy but he makes it harder. He is like a dictator, impossible to have a friendly relationship with him as student-prof. He explains 3 chapters in one lecture, usually 16-18 chapters of the course are given in the winter, with him in the summer time he wants to teach you like 30 chapters.
Uses other peoples examples in class. Doesn't know what he has in his notes, since he took them from different places and didn't write them all himself. Mumbles and nobody even goes to class
He mumbles in the air......definitely not Real Time.
Nice guy, friendly to talk to.  He was good in this class, but again, too much work for a summer course.

Nice guy but giving out too many works.  Can you imagine I have to do 4-5 hws, 2 quizzes, 1 mid-term,  1 presentation, 1 final in the shorter summer semester?  He gotta understand ppl are not taking just one course every semester.  Tests are hard too.

Very good prof for Networking.  His explanations were always clear, the homework was just enough to make you understand everything but wasn't too long.  Only negative was the lectures, they were boring, but we had a break after 1h (2h summer class)!
I don't know what he's like for other courses, but he was good while teaching networking/internetworking. Proof: check out the final marks for this course (very impressive!)
Avoid at all cost.he is a good programmer at best. it is a shame for him to teach.
it takes a long time to do the assignments, but he was a good teacher for this course..however the lectures are boring, so just bring a pillow to the lectures!
